The article is a presidential memorandum from May 24, 2016, in which President Barack Obama delegates authority to the Secretary of State under Section 106 of the Bipartisan Congressional Trade Priorities and Accountability Act of 2015. The memorandum grants the Secretary of State the functions and authorities vested in the President by the Act, with the requirement to inform the United States Trade Representative of any decision to invoke an exception under the Act. The Secretary of State is also authorized to redelegate authority and assign functions to officers of other departments or agencies within the executive branch, as permitted by law. The memorandum is to be published in the Federal Register.